x4freetext: EXPERIMENTAL DETAIL.
GAMMA RAYS RESULTING FROM NON-ELASTIC PROCESSES OF
14.2 MEV NEUTRONS WITH SODIUM, MAGNESIUM, SILICON,
SULPHUR, TITANIUM, CHROMIUM AND IRON.
COCKCROFT-WALTON ACCELERATOR.
DEUTERON-TRITIUM, 200 KEV DEUTERON.
ALL SAMPLES ARE NATURAL. RIGHT CYLINDERS 6 CM DIA.,
12 CM LONG.
DIRECT DETECTION OF GAMMA-RAYS.
NAI(TL) CRYSTAL, 3 INCH * 3 INCH,
.OVERALL ENERGY RESOLUTION IS THE ORDER OF 8.5 PERC.
ABSOLUTE MEASUREMENT.
GAMMAS.
COMMENT (REF. ETC.) ADAPTED.
THE FOLLOWING SOURCES OF ERROR WERE TAKEN INTO
ACCOUNT (IN PERCENT)
- TOTAL NEUTRON COUNTING (LESS THAN 1 )
- DETERMINATION OF PHOTOPEAK EFFICIENCY (3 TO 4)
- DETERMINATION OF PHOTOPEAK AREA (5 TO 20 DEPENDING
ON LINE INTENSITY)
THESE ERRORS HAVE BEEN QUADRATICALLY ADDED TO GIVE
THE EXPERIMENTAL ERROR.
-NO CORRECTION FOR ABSORPTION AND MULTIPLE SCATTERING
IN SAMPLES.
